  * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *

  Function :   This Edit macro may be used to create block characters
  ----------   in text.

  Command syntax : BIG character
  ---------------- BIG HELP or HE

  Use :        Type BIG on the COMMAND line followed by a character
  -----        (A-Z, 0-9, $, # or @), set the cursor in the text where
               you want the block character, and press ENTER, as i.e. :
               COMMAND ===> BIG A
               001100   Data ...   - <===
               001200   Data ...  (CURSOR)
               001300   Data ...
               001400   Data ...
               001500   Data ...
               001600   Data ...
               001700   Data ...
               001800   Data ...
               001900   Data ...
               002000   Data ...
               002100   Data ...
               Result :
               001100   Data ...     AAAAAAAAAA
               001200   Data ...    AAAAAAAAAAAA
               001300   Data ...    AA        AA
               001400   Data ...    AA        AA
               001500   Data ...    AA        AA
               001600   Data ...    AAAAAAAAAAAA
               001700   Data ...    AAAAAAAAAAAA
               001800   Data ...    AA        AA
               001900   Data ...    AA        AA
               002000   Data ...    AA        AA
               002100   Data ...    AA        AA
